def: Land granted by the crown to a thane or lord. Burrill.
The male of any species of goose.
The science of motion; kinematics. [R.] Weisbach.
To go side by side with; hence, to pass by; to outrun and getbefore; as, a dog cotes a hare. [Obs.] Drayton.We coted them on the way, and hither are they coming. Shak.
A fossil resin, so called from its strong, peculiar, pleasantodor.

To give pain or sorrow to; to afflict; hence, to oppress orinjure in one's rights; to bear heavily upon; -- now commonly used inthe passive TO be aggrieved.Aggrieved by oppression and extortion. Macaulay.
A veal cutlet variously seasoned garnished, often with lemon,sardines, and capers.
Bear baiting with a dog. Hudibras.
